other_tests.findings: A dilated fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 14 mm is noted with moderate periappendiceal inflammatory stranding and multiple reactive lymph nodes measuring up to 8 mm in short axis. Otherwise, there is no perforation, periappendiceal fluid collections, or abscesses.
Vital Signs on admission: T 98.3, HR 87, BP 141/94, RR 19, O2 Sats 99% RA.
